    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-12-06T04:24:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-12-06T04:24:00-05:00" n="164"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d164">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">701.60 i 11/12: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Estonia, Latvia, and Lithunia</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Coleman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Riga</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-12-06T11:00:00+01:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 6, 1923—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 6, 11:05 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>88. A. Piip, appointed Esthonian Minister to the United States, sails on <hi
                        rend="italic">Aquitania</hi> December 18, will arrive Washington 27th. He
                    has full powers to arrange for settlement of the Esthonian debt.<note n="8a"
                        xml:id="d164fn8a">For negotiations with the World War Foreign Debt
                        Commission and text of agreement signed Oct. 28, 1925, see <hi rend="italic"
                            >Combined Annual Reports of the World War Foreign Debt Commission</hi>,
                        1922–1926 (Washington, Government Printing Office, 1927), pp. 205 ff.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Coleman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
